    {
        "content": "<p>pchickey opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13500\">PR #13500</a> from <code>pchickey:pch/export_lookup</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The <code>wasmtime::component::Instance</code> struct had getter methods that accepted <code>impl InstanceExportLookup</code>, a pseudo-sealed trait (via <code>#[doc(hidden)]</code>) with impls for &amp;str, String, or ComponentExportIndex.</p>\n<p>Conversely, the <code>wasmtime::component::Component</code> struct had <code>get_export</code> and <code>get_export_index</code> methods which took arguments <code>instance: Option&lt;&amp;ComponentExportIndex&gt;</code> and <code>name: &amp;str</code>.</p>\n<p>This PR renames the trait to <code>ExportLookup</code>, with the exact same impls, and modifies the <code>Component::get_export[_index]</code> methods to take <code>impl ExportLookup</code> instead of <code>&amp;str</code> arguments.</p>\n<p>This is motivated by a follow-up PR that will add <code>wit_parser::ItemName</code> as another type that impls ExportIndex.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 598200763,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1779924508
    },
